WRITING.TEXT: I am praying for you as I type this. I am going through/have been through a very similar situation. I am 21 and would have been married for 2 years on the 19th. I can identify with you so much. Okay here's the backstory. Back in 2010 I started at a new school for my senior year and almost immediately fell for a girl. Sadly she did not share the feelings. After pursuing her for about a year and a half. She finally agreed to date me. We fell in love fast and after a few months I knew I wanted to spend my life with her, and she reciprocated the feelings. After seeking counsel with our parents, I proposed and we set out on the road of getting married. Fast Forward to early of last year, my wife begins talking about divorce and wanting "freedom" and "independence". Later that year in May she went to volunteer all week at a Film Festival. She did so against my wishes seeing as we were planning a big trip the week after. Tensions were high between the two of us the whole week. God ended up providing us with the money to still go the trip and so we went. Later that year, last August, she came to me and told me she was unhappy, I told her I understood because we had been going through a rough time lately. She proceeded to tell me very seriously that she wanted a divorce. Told her that we biblically could not do that and she then told me that while at the festival, nearly three months back, she had brought a man back to her hotel room one night, after we had a fight over the phone. This absolutely devastated me. I completely know of the numbness that you mentioned. Jump to today, we are no longer together. Now I say all this purely so that you can know: you are not alone, I empathize for you deeply, I pray for the best and for healing. If you ever need to talk to someone you think can understand your pain, PM me. I want to help if I can. Love and peace, A brother in Christ.
